-- Gold Futures Decline for First Time in Three Days on Comex in New York
-- B y   P a t r i c k   M c K i e r n a n
-- 2010-12-29T13:26:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-29/gold-futures-decline-for-first-time-in-three-days-on-comex-in-new-york.html
Gold futures for February delivery
fell $3.70, or 0.3 percent, to $1,401.90 an ounce at 8:26 a.m.
on the Comex in New York. Yesterday, the metal jumped 1.6
percent, the most in seven weeks. On Dec. 27, the price gained
0.2 percent.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Patrick McKiernan at 
 pmckiernan@bloomberg.net  